casebody.data:
Deano S. ESPOSITA, Appellant,
v.
SUNTRUST BANK, Amy C. Esposita, Regions Bank d/b/a Amsouth Bank and Magnolia Plantation Homeowners Association, Inc., Appellees. Case No. 5D17-3552 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Fifth District. Opinion filed February 2, 2018
Rehearing and Rehearing En Banc Denied March 26, 2018 Deano S. Esposita, Lake Mary, pro se. Charles P. Gufford, of McCalla Raymer Leibert Pierce, LLC, Orlando, for Appellee, SunTrust Bank. No appearance for other Appellees. ON CONFESSION OF ERROR PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to SunTrust Bank's Confession of Error, we reverse the Summary Final Judgment of Foreclosure, as the trial court lacked jurisdiction to enter the judgment because the case had been removed to federal court. We remand this matter to the trial court for further proceedings.

REVERSED and REMANDED.

SAWAYA, ORFINGER, and LAMBERT, JJ., concur.
